The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Sreesanth gets final warning
                                                   Sreesanth gets final warning
                      
	Kochi: Indian crickets enfant terrible Sreesanth has been given a final warning by the Board of Control for Cricket in India to mend his on-field behaviour, failing which he would be suspended from domestic matches.         
	The latest BCCI missive, dated October 5, was sent to the Kerala Cricket Association (KCA) secretary TC Mathews, to be handed to the player.         
	BCCI has warned Sreesanth against repeating the on-field misbehaviour he showed during the recent Irani Cup in Nagpur.         
	You are hereby given a final warning to ensure that you do not violate the BCCI Code of Conduct. Any repetition of such behavior will be dealt with severely by the BCCI, including suspension from domestic cricket matches, the letter read.           (PTI)                                                                                                                   
